sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Agent as Agent
    participant LLM as LLM (stateless)
    participant Tools as Built-in Tools
    participant MCP as MCP Servers
    participant Subs as Sub-Agents

    User->>Agent: prompt

    Note over Agent: Load project rules + memory
    Agent->>MCP: tools/list (discover MCP tools)
    MCP-->>Agent: [{name, schema}, ...]
    Note over Agent: Merge built-in + MCP tools

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 1 — Understand
    Agent->>LLM: call #1 (context + all tool schemas)
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Read(file)
    Agent->>Tools: Read (syscall open+read)
    Tools-->>Agent: file contents

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 2 — Research (parallel sub-agents)
    Agent->>LLM: call #2 (enriched context)
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Agent x2

    par Parallel execution
        Agent->>Subs: fork Sub-Agent A
        Subs->>LLM: own LLM calls
        Subs->>Tools: Grep, Read...
        Subs->>MCP: mcp__github__search
        Subs-->>Agent: result A
    and
        Agent->>Subs: fork Sub-Agent B
        Subs->>LLM: own LLM calls
        Subs->>Tools: Glob, Read...
        Subs-->>Agent: result B
    end
    Note over Agent: join(A, B)

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 3 — Act (with permission)
    Agent->>LLM: call #3 (full context)
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Edit(file)
    Agent->>User: Permission gate — confirm?
    User-->>Agent: Approved
    Agent->>Tools: Edit (syscall write)
    Tools-->>Agent: OK

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 4 — Notify (remote MCP)
    Agent->>LLM: call #4
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: mcp__slack__send
    Agent->>MCP: JSON-RPC tools/call (SSE)
    MCP-->>Agent: message sent

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 5 — Conclude
    Agent->>LLM: call #5
    LLM-->>Agent: final text
    Agent->>User: Display result
    Note over Agent: Save memory if relevant
